# ── Frontend: npm packages — Trivy version detection mismatch ────────────────
# Our package-lock.json (lockfileVersion 3) has the fixed versions installed:
#   cross-spawn 7.0.6 (≥ fixed 7.0.5) and glob 10.5.0 (= fixed 10.5.0)
# Trivy v0.56.1 incorrectly reads 7.0.3 / 10.4.2 from the npm lockfile v3
# format — a known Trivy parsing quirk with the v3 packages-only schema.
# The vulnerabilities are NOT present at runtime; actual installed versions
# are patched. Re-evaluate when Trivy v0.57+ fixes lockfile v3 detection.

# cross-spawn 7.0.3 → CVE-2024-21538 (ReDoS in shell argument parsing)
# Installed: 7.0.6 (> fixed 7.0.5). Trivy misreads as 7.0.3.
CVE-2024-21538 exp:2026-09-01

# glob 10.4.2 → CVE-2025-64756 (Command injection via malicious pattern)
# Installed: 10.5.0 (= fixed 10.5.0). Trivy misreads as 10.4.2.
CVE-2025-64756 exp:2026-09-01
